================================================================================
Third-party work evaluated and acknowledged
================================================================================

Three existing public projects were examined as wrapper candidates before
this library was written. None of them ported cleanly to current Apple
Shortcuts, current Python ergonomics, or both, so a hand-written schema
layer was developed. Each project still informed parts of the design:

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Open-Jellycore — https://github.com/OpenJelly/Open-Jellycore
Copyright the Open-Jellycore contributors. Licensed under GPL-3.0.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A Swift compiler-frontend for Apple Shortcuts (the Jellycuts language).
The most comprehensive open catalogue of first-party action identifiers,
parameter key names, OS-min metadata, and typed enums.

`data/jellycore_facts.json` in this repository is a derivative compilation
of Open-Jellycore's curated lookup tables, produced by
`scripts/extract_jellycore.py` walking an Open-Jellycore checkout and
projecting it to JSON. It is licensed under GPL-3.0-or-later (the same
licence as this project at large). The derivative status of the JSON is
the basis for this project's choice of GPL-3.0-or-later. The dataset is
a development-time bootstrapping artefact for
`scripts/coverage_report.py` and is excluded from the built wheel
(`pyproject.toml` `[tool.hatch.build.targets.wheel] exclude = ["data/"]`).

Modifications to the upstream catalogue (per GPL-3.0 §5(a)):

- 2026-05-08: subset projection to JSON via
  `scripts/extract_jellycore.py`. Only Apple-side facts are emitted —
  identifier strings, Apple display names, parameter WF* key names, and
  OS-min metadata. Upstream original expression (description prose, the
  Jellycuts DSL function names, upstream Swift parameter-struct names,
  presets) is filtered out.
- 2026-05-08: typo fix — `WFShell` enum value `/usr/bin/pearl` corrected
  to `/usr/bin/perl`. Worth upstreaming back to Open-Jellycore.
- 2026-05-08: filtered out Open-Jellycore-invented identifiers
  (`jelly.config.*`) from `structural_identifiers`.
- 2026-05-08: dropped the unused `enums` section (Open-Jellycore's
  typed-enum extraction was bootstrapping data that this library never
  consumed at runtime).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
shortcuts-js — https://github.com/joshfarrant/shortcuts-js
Copyright (c) Josh Farrant. Licensed under MIT.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A TypeScript library for building shortcuts (~iOS 12 era). Informed this
project's per-action factory pattern, the auto-mint-output-UUID convention,
and the variable type taxonomy (`Ask`, `Clipboard`, `CurrentDate`,
`ExtensionInput`, `Variable`). Not vendored — the schema source code is
hand-written from decoded Apple samples; shortcuts-js was a hint source.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
iOS-Shortcuts-Reference — https://github.com/sebj/iOS-Shortcuts-Reference
Copyright (c) sebj. Archived 2022; licence not declared.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A reference data repository (not a library). Informed top-level metadata
enum modelling — `WFWorkflowImportQuestions`, `WFWorkflowInputContentItemClasses`,
`WFWorkflowTypes`, the icon-colour palette, `shortcuts://` URL schemes.
Not vendored.

